      • strToCongruentToNModMRightPadZero

        public static java.lang.String strToCongruentToNModMRightPadZero(java.lang.String str,
                                                                 int residue,
                                                                 int mod)
        Right-pads the given string with zeros so that its size is congruent to a given residue modulo a given modulus. Ultimately, we'd have: |str + B| % mod = residue where B is a string of 0's. This is used in MD4 algorithm.
        Parameters:
        str - the given string
        residue - the given residue
        mod - the given modulus
        Returns:
        the padded string with the required size
